<subSubSection id="04E56516A929FFEFEFF3FCA75C71FC43" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4C40369DA929FFEFEFF3FCA75C71FC43" blockId="3.[136,1452,410,976]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="7E8BEA8FA929FFEFEFF3FCA75C29FCD3" bold="true" box="[189,328,806,832]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">Comments:</emphasis>
—First record for the Neotropics and 
<collectingCountry id="34E8760DA929FFEFEDBEFCA65E46FCD2" box="[752,807,807,833]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">Peru</collectingCountry>
. It was found in branches of small shrubs associated with cryoturbed soils, and it represents one of the records at higher altitudes of 
<taxonomicName id="8BFF4D1EA929FFEFECFBFCCA5935FCF6" box="[949,1108,843,869]" class="Myxomycetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="class">Myxomycetes</taxonomicName>
in the world. Morphologically, it resembles 
<taxonomicName id="8BFF4D1EA929FFEFEE54FCEF5E46FC1A" authority="(Ditmar) Rostaf. (1875: 259)" authorityName="Rostaf." authorityPageNumber="259" authorityYear="1875" baseAuthorityName="Ditmar" box="[282,807,878,905]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Trichiaceae" genus="Trichia" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Trichiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="contorta">
<emphasis id="7E8BEA8FA929FFEFEE54FCEF5CB3FC1B" box="[282,466,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">Trichia contorta</emphasis>
(Ditmar) Rostaf. (1875: 259)
</taxonomicName>
, but it is distinguished by the smaller spores, 11–14 µm diam. 
<emphasis id="7E8BEA8FA929FFEFEF81FC125D8CFC3F" box="[207,237,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">vs.</emphasis>
14–15 µm diam. in 
<taxonomicName id="8BFF4D1EA929FFEFEE9DFC125F35FC3F" box="[467,596,914,940]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Trichiaceae" genus="Trichia" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Trichiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="7E8BEA8FA929FFEFEE9DFC125F35FC3F" box="[467,596,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">T. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the length of the pointed free ends, 10–20 µm long 
<emphasis id="7E8BEA8FA929FFEFEB99FC125997FC3F" box="[1239,1270,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">vs.</emphasis>
8–9 µm long in 
<emphasis id="7E8BEA8FA929FFEFEFC6FC365C71FC43" box="[136,272,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">
<taxonomicName id="8BFF4D1EA929FFEFEFC6FC365C6CFC43" box="[136,269,950,976]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Trichiaceae" genus="Trichia" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Trichiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="mirabilis">T. mirabilis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
